coln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":60,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":69,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":104,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh Darfield was born in 1155, in Darfield, Yorkshire, England. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1155–":"1155–Surnud","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1155":"1155","1230":"1230","Darfield, Yorkshire, England":"Darfield, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1155–":"1155–Kuollut","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","1155–Male":"1155–Kuollut","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1155":"1155","1230":"1230","Darfield, Yorkshire, England":"Da